# Build: NFC Items Page (`app/(admin)/nfc-items/page.js`)

## Context
Refer to CLAUDE.md for full project context, stack, folder structure, database schema, and Supabase client conventions before writing any code. This page lives inside the admin layout shell ‚Äî do not rebuild the sidebar or header.

---

## What to build

A single page at `app/(admin)/nfc-items/page.js` that contains two things:

1. A data table listing all NFC items in the system
2. A "Create NFC Item" modal/dialog that opens over the table

This is a **Client Component** (`'use client'`) ‚Äî it manages table data, modal state, and form state locally.

---

## Performance requirements

- On mount, fetch all NFC items in a **single Supabase query** ‚Äî join the owner's email from `auth.users` via `users_roles` in one call, do not make separate per-row requests
- Use `useMemo` to derive filtered/sorted table data ‚Äî never re-filter on every render
- Optimistic UI on status toggle ‚Äî update the local state immediately on toggle click, then fire the Supabase update in the background. If the update fails, revert the local state and show an inline error.
- Optimistic UI on delete ‚Äî remove the row from local state immediately, then fire the delete. If it fails, re-insert the row and show an error.
- Debounce the search input ‚Äî 300ms delay before filtering, using `useCallback` + `useRef` for the timer. Do not install a debounce library.
- Paginate client-side ‚Äî show 10 rows per page. Do not fetch pages from the server separately; fetch all at once and slice locally.

