## Create NFC Item modal

### Trigger
The "Create NFC Item" button in the page header opens this modal. Use shadcn/ui `Dialog`.

### Form fields

**Customer name** ‚Äî text input, required. Label: "Customer name". Placeholder: "e.g. Kofi Mensah".

**Customer email** ‚Äî email input, required. Label: "Customer email". Placeholder: "kofi@example.com". Validate format client-side before submit.

**Product type** ‚Äî shadcn/ui `Select`, required. Label: "Product type". Options:
- Card
- Stand
- Round Tag

**Slug** ‚Äî text input. Label: "Profile URL slug". Shows a read-only prefix before the input: `beemhive.com/t/` rendered in muted text. The input itself accepts the slug portion only. Rules: lowercase, alphanumeric, hyphens allowed, no spaces, no special characters ‚Äî enforce with an `onChange` sanitiser that strips invalid characters as the user types. Below the input, show a live preview of the full URL in muted small text: `https://beemhive.com/t/{slug}`. Include a "Generate random" button (dice icon, `Shuffle` from lucide-react) next to the input that populates a random 6-character alphanumeric slug.

### Validation (client-side, before any Supabase call)
- Customer name: required, min 2 characters
- Customer email: required, valid email format
- Product type: required, must be one of the three options
- Slug: required, min 3 characters, max 30, matches `/^[a-z0-9-]+$/`, no leading or trailing hyphens

Show validation errors inline below each field in small `rose-500` text. Do not show all errors at once on first load ‚Äî only show a field's error after the user has interacted with it (touched/blurred) or after a failed submit attempt.

### On submit

1. Disable all inputs and show "Creating‚Ä¶" on the button with a spinner
2. Check slug uniqueness: query `nfc_items` for an existing row with the same slug. If it exists, show an inline error on the slug field: "This slug is already taken ‚Äî try another" and stop.
3. Insert into `nfc_items` ‚Äî `slug`, `product_type`, `owner_id` (the newly created user's ID)
4. Insert into `profiles` ‚Äî `user_id` with empty defaults
5. Call `supabase.auth.admin.inviteUserByEmail(email)` from a **Next.js API route** (`app/api/invite/route.js`) ‚Äî never call admin auth methods from the client. The API route uses the service role client.
6. On success:
   - Close the modal
   - Prepend the new row to the top of the local table state (optimistic ‚Äî no refetch)
   - Show a shadcn/ui `Toast` notification: "NFC item created ‚Äî invite sent to {email}"
7. On any error:
   - Re-enable the form
   - Show a non-dismissible error banner inside the modal above the submit button: "Something went wrong: {mapped error message}. Please try again."

### Success state inside the modal (shown before closing)

Before the modal auto-closes (after a 1.5s delay), briefly show a success screen inside the modal:
- A green checkmark animation (CSS only, no library)
- "Item created successfully"
- The generated profile URL in a copyable code block: `https://beemhive.com/t/{slug}`
- NFC Tools instruction in a muted info box:
  > Open NFC Tools on your phone ‚Üí tap Write ‚Üí URL ‚Üí paste the link above ‚Üí tap your NFC card

